    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - ADJUSTMENTS - fender mounted mirrors- install</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>fender mounted mirrors- install</title>
        <figure id="f0900866" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900866.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 66. Fender Mounted Mirror Assembly - Install</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FENDER MOUNTED MIRROR BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MIRROR HEAD</callout1>
                <callout1>3. LATERAL BRACE MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an assistant holding the mirror assembly, locate and align the bracket mounting holes
                and the fender mounting holes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the mounting bolts through the bracket base and fender section. Install the flat
                washer and lock nut on the underside of the fender section and hand tighten (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900866">Figure 66, Item 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate and align the lateral bracket base hole with the mounting hole in the side section of
                the hood assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the mounting bolt through the base and hood section. Install the flat washer and lock
                nut.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten all nuts. (See Torque chart for values)</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure for the opposite side mirror assembly.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
